From: Timo Könnecke <mo@mowerk.net>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] nemo: dts: disable cont-splash and ULPS for display bringup

The nemo panel DTS has qcom,cont-splash-enabled set in both panel
nodes, but msm8926-nemo-panel.dtsi simultaneously deletes
qcom,memblock-reserve from mdss_fb0 via /delete-property/.  The MDSS
driver then detects "continuous splash enabled" but fails to reserve
the splash memory, leaving the display subsystem in a broken
half-initialized state: setPowerMode(NORMAL) returns 0 but the DSI
panel never turns on, and a subsequent FBIOBLANK(POWERDOWN) followed
by FBIOBLANK(UNBLANK) hangs the kernel waiting for an ULPS exit that
never completes.

Remove qcom,cont-splash-enabled so the driver performs a clean
cold-start DSI panel initialization on the first FBIOBLANK(UNBLANK)
call from the hwcomposer.  Also remove qcom,ulps-enabled for now to
avoid the ULPS-exit hang on blank/unblank cycles while pinctrl for the
DSI controller is not available (mdss_dsi_pinctrl_init logs "failed to
get pinctrl" at probe time because no pinctrl-names/pinctrl-0/1 are
defined in the DSI node).  Both properties can be revisited once the
display is confirmed working.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [nemo-specific port patch]

diff --git a/arch/arm/boot/dts/msm8926-nemo/msm8926-nemo-panel.dtsi b/arch/arm/boot/dts/msm8926-nemo/msm8926-nemo-panel.dtsi
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/msm8926-nemo/msm8926-nemo-panel.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/msm8926-nemo/msm8926-nemo-panel.dtsi
@@ -148,8 +148,6 @@
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-bl-pmic-control-type = "bl_ctrl_dcs_l";
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-reset-sequence = <1 50>;
 		qcom,mdss-brightness-default-level = <208>;
-		qcom,cont-splash-enabled;
-		qcom,ulps-enabled;
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-lp11-init;
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-off-pre-reset-delay = <20>;
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-off-post-reset-delay = <20>;
@@ -380,8 +378,6 @@
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-bl-pmic-control-type = "bl_ctrl_dcs_l";
 		qcom,mdss-dsi-reset-sequence = <1 50>;
 		qcom,mdss-brightness-default-level = <208>;
-		qcom,cont-splash-enabled;
-		qcom,ulps-enabled;
 		qcom,mdss-flip-ud;
 		qcom,blmap = /bits/ 8 <
